docx-cli — third-party notices

This file lists the third-party software docx-cli redistributes (statically
linked into the published binaries via `bun build --compile`, or bundled
into `dist/index.js`), along with the attribution each license requires.

docx-cli itself is licensed under the MIT License (see LICENSE). Linking
permissively-licensed libraries (MIT / Apache-2.0 / BSD-3-Clause) leaves
that license unchanged. Linking the LGPL-3.0 libheif-js library does NOT
make docx-cli copyleft either — LGPL §4 permits use by works under other
licenses provided the conditions in this NOTICES file (acknowledgement +
LGPL-3.0 text + the right to swap in a modified libheif by rebuilding
docx-cli from source) are met.

Whenever a runtime dependency is added or changed in package.json,
re-audit whether the new entry needs an attribution here.


